<refentry xml:id="vtiful-kernel-excel.getPageSetup" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink">
 <refnamediv>
  <refname>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel::getPageSetup</refname>
  <refpurpose>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel getPageSetup</refpurpose>
 </refnamediv>
 <refsect1 role="description">
  &reftitle.description;
  <methodsynopsis>
   <modifier>public</modifier> <type>array</type><methodname>Vtiful\Kernel\Excel::getPageSetup</methodname>
   <void/>
  </methodsynopsis>
  <simpara>Returns the page setup and print margins of the worksheet currently open for reading.</simpara>
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="parameters">
  &reftitle.parameters;
  &no.function.parameters;
 </refsect1>
 <refsect1 role="returnvalues">
  &reftitle.returnvalues;
  <simpara>An associative array with a <literal>margins</literal> key holding the <literal>left</literal>, <literal>right</literal>, <literal>top</literal>, <literal>bottom</literal>, <literal>header</literal> and <literal>footer</literal> margins (or &null; when no margins are defined), together with the page setup attributes such as <literal>paper_size</literal> and <literal>fit_to_width</literal>. Returns &null; when no worksheet is open for reading or no page setup is available.</simpara>
 </refsect1>
</refentry>
